By Vieta's formulas, $a+b=5$ and $ab=9$.  Then
\begin{align*}
(a - 1)(b - 1) &= ab - a - b + 1 \\
&= 9 - 5 + 1 \\
&= \boxed{5}.
\end{align*}

Substitute $a = 4$ into the equation to find $b$: \begin{align*}
3a + 2b &= 12\\
3(4) + 2b &= 12\\
12 + 2b &= 12\\
2b &= 0\\
b &= \boxed{0}
\end{align*}
